24/* JISX0213 plane 1 (= ISO-IR-233) characters are in the range
25 0x{21..7E}{21..7E}.
26 JISX0213 plane 2 (= ISO-IR-229) characters are in the range
27 0x{21,23..25,28,2C..2F,6E..7E}{21..7E}.
28 Together this makes 120 rows of 94 characters.
29*/
30
31/* Tables JISX0213 -> UCS-4. Generated through
32
33 clisp tab.lisp < JISX0213.TXT
34
35 where tab.lisp is:
36 ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
37 (locally (declare (compile))
38 (flet ((row-convert (row)
39 (cond ((<= #x121 row #x17E) (- row 289)) ; 0..93
40 ((= #x221 row) (- row 451)) ; 94
41 ((<= #x223 row #x225) (- row 452)) ; 95..97
42 ((= #x228 row) (- row 454)) ; 98
43 ((<= #x22C row #x22F) (- row 457)) ; 99..102
44 ((<= #x26E row #x27E) (- row 519))))) ; 103..119
45 (let ((table (make-array '(120 94) :initial-element 0))
46 (pagemin (make-array #x1100 :initial-element nil))
47 (pagemax (make-array #x1100 :initial-element nil))
48 (pageidx (make-array #x1100 :initial-element nil))
49 (pagestart (make-array 0 :fill-pointer 0 :adjustable t)))
50 (let ((private-use #x0001))
51 (loop
52 (let ((line (read-line nil nil nil)))
53 (unless line (return))
54 (let ((row (parse-integer line :start 2 :end 5 :radix 16))
55 (col (parse-integer line :start 5 :end 7 :radix 16))
56 ucs)
57 (if (= (length line) 21)
58 (let ((u1 (parse-integer line :start 10 :end 14 :radix 16))
59 (u2 (parse-integer line :start 17 :end 21 :radix 16)))
60 (format t " ~({ 0x~4,'0X, 0x~4,'0X }~),~%" u1 u2)
61 (setf ucs private-use)
62 (incf private-use))
63 (setf ucs (parse-integer line :start 10 :radix 16)))
64 (setf (aref table (row-convert row) (- col #x21)) ucs)))))
65 (format t "~%")
66 (dotimes (rowc 120)
67 (dotimes (colc 94)
68 (let* ((value (aref table rowc colc))
69 (page (ash value -8))
70 (rest (ldb (byte 8 0) value)))
71 (setf (aref pagemin page)
72 (if (aref pagemin page)
73 (min (aref pagemin page) rest)
74 rest))
75 (setf (aref pagemax page)
76 (if (aref pagemax page)
77 (max (aref pagemax page) rest)
78 rest)))))
79 (let ((index 0))
80 (do ((i 0)) ((>= i #x1100))
81 (if (aref pagemin i)
82 (if (and (aref pagemin (1+ i))
83 (>= (aref pagemin i) #x80)
84 (< (aref pagemax (1+ i)) #x80))
85 ; Combine two pages into a single one.
86 (progn
87 (vector-push-extend (+ (ash i 8) #x80) pagestart)
88 (setf (aref pageidx i) index)
89 (setf (aref pageidx (1+ i)) index)
90 (incf index)
91 (incf i 2))
92 ; A single page.
93 (progn
94 (vector-push-extend (ash i 8) pagestart)
95 (setf (aref pageidx i) index)
96 (incf index)
97 (incf i)))
98 (incf i))))
99 (dotimes (row #x300)
100 (let ((rowc (row-convert row)))
101 (when rowc
102 (format t " /\* 0x~X21..0x~X7E *\/~%" row row)
103 (let ((count 0))
104 (dotimes (colc 94)
105 (when (= (mod count 8) 0) (format t " "))
106 (let* ((value (aref table rowc colc))
107 (page (ash value -8))
108 (index (aref pageidx page)))
109 (assert (<= 0 (- value (aref pagestart index)) #xFF))
110 (format t " ~(0x~4,'0X~),"
111 (logior (ash index 8)
112 (- value (aref pagestart index)))))
113 (incf count)
114 (when (= (mod count 8) 0) (format t "~%"))))
115 (format t "~%"))))
116 (format t "~%")
117 (let ((count 0))
118 (dotimes (i (length pagestart))
119 (when (= (mod count 8) 0) (format t " "))
120 (format t " ~7<~(0x~4,'0X~)~>," (aref pagestart i))
121 (incf count)
122 (when (= (mod count 8) 0) (format t "~%"))))
123 (format t "~%"))))
124 ;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;
125*/
126
